      • get

        public V get(K key)
        Retrieves the value of the key stored in the tree. If the key is not in the tree a null value is returned.
        Parameters:
        key - The key to find in the tree.
        Returns:
        The value that's associated with the specified key, returns null if the key is not found.

      • put

                V value)
        Inserts the key (with associated value) into the tree.
        Parameters:
        key - The key to insert.
        value - The value associated with the key. Can not be null.

      • size

        public int size()
        Returns the number of nodes in our tree.
        Returns:

      • keys

        public java.lang.Iterable<TwoThreeTree.KeyValuePair> keys()
        Returns an iterable collection of all key/values in our tree.
        Returns:

      • keys

        public java.lang.Iterable<TwoThreeTree.KeyValuePair> keys(K lo,
                                                          K hi)
        Returns an iterable collection of all key/values in our tree.
        Parameters:
        lo - The lowest key value that should occur in our collection.
        hi - The highest key value that should occur in our collection.
        Returns:
        A LinkedList with the elements sorted by key order within the bounds of lo =< keys =< hi.

      • depth

        public int depth()
        Returns the depth of the entire tree, since it's a balanced tree the depth is the same in the entire tree.
        Returns:
        The depth as an int. A tree with just one node (root) will have a depth of 0.

      • howMuchMore

        public int howMuchMore()
        Returns the maximum number of elements we can add to the tree before our depth changes.
        Returns:
        Returns the remaining elements we can add before our tree grows in depth.

      • density

        public float density()
        Returns the average value of two and threeNodes in our tree.
        Returns:
        The value as a float.
